# Week 2 — Controller Design Results

## PID Controller
- Gains: P=50, I=2, D=10
- Settling time: ~0.4 seconds
- Manual tuning required

## LQR Controller  
- Q = diag([1,1,2000,10])
- R = 1
- K = [-1.0, -2.31, 25.91, 5.37]
- Settling time: ~0.5 seconds
- Mathematically optimal gains
- No manual tuning required

## Conclusion
LQR outperforms PID in smoothness and optimality.
PID settles faster but LQR is more robust.
Real hardware tuning required in Week 5.
